solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    string breakPalindrome(string palindrome) {
        int n = palindrome.size();
        if (n == 1) return "";
        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; ++i) {
            if (palindrome[i] != 'a') {
                palindrome[i] = 'a';
                return palindrome;
            }
        }
        palindrome.back() = 'b';
        return palindrome;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Scan the first half of the string; the first non-'a' character is replaced with 'a' to achieve the lexicographically smallest non-palindrome. If all are 'a', the last character is set to 'b'. Single-character strings cannot be broken, so return empty.

